Defendant Keshawn E Palmer in court with attorney Ann R Auberry.  James W Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following:

The Court imposed but stayed 9 months at the House of Correction, credit for 5 days time served, Huber and good time, and placed  defendant on probation for one (1) year.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with co-defendant Billy Ray Jackson;
 - No contact with the address of the offense at 2923 North 12th Street, city and county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin; no contact with any vacant or foreclosed on house;
 - Must obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Perform 50 hours community service;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, plus all costs and disbursements by the end of the probationary period.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

No restitution information was requested; therefore, Court set restitution at zero.

Should defendant successfully complete all conditions set forth by the Court and the Probation Department, pay all costs and surcharges, and have no new contacts with the criminal justice system arising to the level of probable cause, Court would consider petition for expungement.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
